16/09/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- The country set another record in tourism this year, with the tourism ministry announcing on Tuesday (September 15th) that more than two million people visited between January and August. That's a 42.5% increase compared to the same period a year ago. According to the ministry, more than 90% of the visitors were on holiday; the rest were making business or day trips. (Top News, Ora News, Top Channel - 15/09/09)
